<h2>Tools and Integrations</h2>

<p>School management system integration is the primary trigger for attendance data. Most school management software offers API or export options. WhatsApp Business API provides significantly higher open rates than SMS for parent communication. For payment reminders, accounting system integration or a simple calendar-based flow is sufficient.</p>

<BlogCTA sector="Education" sectorSlug="egitim" variant="inline" />

<h2>Real Scenario: What Changes in a Week?</h2>

<p><strong>Institution:</strong> Istanbul private elementary school with 280 students. Absence notification by phone, payment tracking in Excel.</p>

<p><strong>Before automation:</strong> Administrative staff mark arriving students each morning, then call parents of absent students one by one. At the start of each week, they also call parents with overdue payments.</p>

<p><strong>4 weeks later:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>When attendance is entered into the system, an automatic WhatsApp message goes to parents of absent students — morning phone calls are gone</li>
  <li>Automatic reminder sent to parents 3 days before payment date — late payment rate dropped 40%</li>
  <li>Exam date announcement reached all parents in 2 minutes (previously class by class manually)</li>
  <li>Administrative team saved 12 hours per week</li>
</ul>

<h2>Common Mistakes</h2>

<h3>Mistake 1: Sending messages without parent consent</h3>
<p>Before starting communication automation, collect parent preferences on which channel they want to receive messages. Both a legal requirement and a trust issue.</p>

<h3>Mistake 2: Reducing absence notification to a single step</h3>
<p>Some schools send an absence notification and think the process is complete. What happens if the parent doesn't respond should also be included in the flow.</p>

<h2>Where Should You Start?</h2>

<ul class="questions-list">
  <li>Is the daily time spent on absence notification more than 1 hour?</li>
  <li>Is the payment late rate above 15%?</li>
  <li>Are parent notifications sent class by class separately?</li>
  <li>Does enrollment season require a dedicated team member for form tracking?</li>
  <li>Does preparing a term report take more than 1 day?</li>
</ul>

